  <excursions><![CDATA[<p><strong>PRE-BOOKABLE - Excursions are available from 13 May 20 unless stated otherwise</strong></p>
<h2>Siena &amp; San Gimignano</h2>
<p>From £77 Thursdays &amp; Sundays, full day. </p>
<p>Pick up time: 8.50am / Drop off time: 7.00pm</p>
<p>A guided tour of the medieval town of Siena which includes: the cathedral, music academy and the Accademia Chigiana. In the afternoon drive through the Chianti hills to explore San Gimignano, a town of towers dating back to the Etruscan period. Not suitable for people with mobility issues.</p>
<h2>Florence with the Uffizi Gallery</h2>
<p>From £77 Friday, full day</p>
<p>Pick up time: 9.00am / Drop off time: 5pm</p>
<p><br /><span>Visit the home town of the famous Medici family, wealthy patrons of the famous writers, artists, architects and sculptors who flocked to the city. Leonardo De Vinci, Michelangelo, Botticelli, Raphael to name a few, filling the churches palaces and streets with the world’s greatest Renaissance works. Our excellent guide will share all the secret stories and make the city alive in front of your eyes. The walk will end by the famous Uffizi Gallery where you will be able to SKIP THE QUEUE (entrance fee payable locally). </span></p>
<h2>Cinque Terre</h2>
<p>From £90 Tuesdays &amp; Saturdays, full day</p>
<p>Pick up time: 7.20am / Drop off time: 7.00pm </p>
<p>Travelling by boat and/or train (weather permitting) around the Cinque Terre discover some of the most picturesque seaside villages in the Mediterranean. Starting at Riomaggiore or Manarola, and passing all five villages with their colourful houses stopping at: Vernazza and Monterosso where there is time for lunch and swimming. Not suitable for people with mobility issues</p>
<p>*<strong>Please note that the pick up and drop off point for all excursions is the Montecatini Tourist Office located in the centre of town approx. 10 minutes walk from hotels. </strong></p>
<p><strong>BOOK LOCALLY</strong> <em>Prices are shown for guidance only.</em></p>
<h2>Pisa</h2>
<p>From £63 Monday, full day<br />A guided tour will tell you all secrets of the Piazza dei Miracoli and why it leans. But, Pisa is not just about the ‘Square of Miracles’ – the tour continues to the Piazza dei Cavalieri (Knights Square) and the old monumental palaces of the town.</p>
<h2>Vinci &amp; Wine</h2>
<p>From £59 Thursday, full day<br />A journey into the charming town of Vinci, the home of famous Leonardo Da Vinci, where you can also visit a museum dedicated to the genius' inventions. Then onto a traditional farmhouse which has amazing views over the vineyards and olive groves. A small boutique Winery, handed down through the family for generations, will spoil your taste buds with 4 of the famous Chianti di Monte Albano wines. Three reds and one white, will be accompanied with delicious bruschettas and locally produced pecorino, prosciutto and Tuscan salami.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em><em>Please note we act at all times as selling agent for </em><em>the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions. See</em> <a href="/{localLink:66d6dfd2-b127-48e8-b6d8-228d6e59ea65}" title="Terms &amp; Conditions"><em>terms &amp; conditions.</em></a></em></p>]]></excursions>
